## Color Usage Guidelines

### Primary Yellow (#E2C33D)
**Use For:**
- Primary action buttons
- Active navigation items
- Links and CTAs
- Important badges/labels
- Progress indicators
- Selected states

**⚠️ Accessibility Warning:**
Yellow on white has poor contrast. ALWAYS use dark text on yellow:
```css
.btn-primary {
  background: var(--color-primary);
  color: var(--text-on-primary); /* Black text */
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold); /* Improve readability */
}
```

### Secondary Dark Slate (#1F2937)
**Use For:**
- Secondary buttons
- Headers/footers
- Text on light backgrounds
- Borders for emphasis
- Alternative UI elements

### Color Combinations That Work

#### ✅ High Contrast (Accessible)
```css
/* Yellow + Black */
background: var(--color-primary);
color: var(--color-neutral-900);

/* Dark Slate + White */
background: var(--color-secondary);
color: white;

/* White + Black text */
background: white;
color: var(--color-neutral-900);
```

#### ⚠️ Avoid These Combinations
```css
/* Low contrast - fails WCAG */
❌ Yellow on white: color: #E2C33D; background: white;
❌ Yellow on light gray: color: #E2C33D; background: #F5F7FA;
❌ Light yellow on white: color: #F5E9A8; background: white;
```

